Line11.E2C66: Go to his shrine. Honor him there. Perhaps he will commune with Túr Dúlra's savior.
Line3.E2C66: You’ve healed this place, but the spirits here still ache with rot. It was their cries you heard.
Line5.E2C66: They don’t listen when we call back. Their pain...
Line9.E2C66: There is one who might help. The spirit Gathlen. He's a healer of his kind. (pained groan) Or he was, until the college fell.
MenuLabel: “Túr Dúlra called out to me in pain.”
